	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64607739"><p>US-style fair use is far more flexible than English-style fair dealing and its various counterparts in other jurisdictions. The key distinction is that the US system relies on 4 general criteria to determine applicability, while the English system only applies to a few specifically enumerated situations. Even a right to private copying that was explicitly created by our legislature was rapidly <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/quashing-of-private-copying-exception" title="www.gov.uk">quashed<span class="substr"> </span></a> [www.gov.uk] when Big Copyright started a formal legal challenge. There is, as far as I can see, absolutely zero chance</p></div>
	</div>

