	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64606771"><p><div class="quote"><p>That's what they said about black people not too long ago.</p></div><p>They were wrong about that, but this is different from that. The computer doesn't think. It just processes. LLMs produce profound results, but they also produce hilarious results, and the nature of the hilarity proves the lack of thought. The process by which an LLM produces an image is more like digestion than cogitation. There's no reflection in the process that would shape it as intelligence does. As you draw something by hand using your brain you re-evaluate it in realtime. Every letter, every brush str<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64606771">

</div>
</div>

