		<div id="comment_body_64606361"><p>While U.S. law provides there is an implied copyright on any original text, even if it is made public, I put the copyright symbol on all of my Web pages.  I just now added "bing" and "bingbot" to my robots.txt file.  Those two user agents of Microsoft appeared in a log of visitors to my Web site.</p><p>However, there are bots, crawlers, and scrapers -- all of which are really the same -- that ignore robots.txt.  Among them are bots run by Amazon and Google.</p></div>
