</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64606287">Just, no. Anything created by a person is copyrighted by that person, and does not need any symbols or statements to make it copyrighted. This is the law in almost all, if not all western countries; and in many other countries as well. It's why you can't copy news stories on the internet unless it meets fair use rules. Same for anyone. AI engines are created for the profit of people or companies, for their good, not the public's. Therefore fair use does not apply.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64606287">
