	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64607393"><p><div class="quote"><p> Like just because the gamepass servers don't have a robot txt on the protocol doesn't make them somehow free for some other dude to use and make copies of.</p></div><p>Partially true. You are free to use something presented to you. The copyright requirements then are related to reproduction. And training an AI model isn't so much "making copies" of actual content, as much as it is transforming them into a, completely unrecognisable from the original, algorithm. And you can't copyright block transformative works.</p></div>
	</div>

